25/05/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Prime Minister Agim Ceku said on Wednesday (24 May) that Kosovo will open an office at the EU's headquarters in Brussels. Speaking after a meeting with UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen, Ceku explained that the liaison office would help address integration issues. Jessen-Petersen, meanwhile, told reporters that the prime minister would attend a UN Security Council session for a debate on Kosovo's future. 
In other news Wednesday, UN special envoy Martti Ahtisaari said he hopes the first round of actual status negotiations will take place at the end of July. His comment followed a meeting with Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic in Helsinki. Ahtisaari said this week's fifth round of talks on decentralisation between teams from Belgrade and Pristina had gone better than expected. (UPI, AP, Tanjug, Beta, UN Web site, KosovaLive - 24/05/06)
